DataElement.preferredName: Gamma-Enolase Laboratory Procedure Performed 3 Decimal Place Microgram per Liter Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 3 decimal place microgram per liter numeric laboratory value measured, assigned or computed related to the assessment of gamma-enolase in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Human gamma-enolase protein (433 aa, approximately 47 kD) is encoded by the ENO2 gene. This neuron-specific enzyme catalyzes the formation of pyruvate from D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate during glycolysis. It is involved in both neurotrophy and neuroprotection._Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting._Executed and carried through to completion.
